UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee v. Forrest Brandon BUXTON, also known as Brandon Buxton, Defendant-Appellant. No. 10-30343

Summary Calendar.

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Jan. 26, 2011. Camille Ann Domingue, Howard Cobb Parker, U.S. Attorney’s Office, Lafayette, LA, Cristina Walker, Shreveport, LA, for Plaintiff-Appellee. Wayne Joseph Blanchard, Assistant Federal Public Defender, Federal Public Defender’s Office, Western District of Louisiana, Lafayette, LA, for Defendant-Appellant.

Before HIGGINBOTHAM, SMITH, and HAYNES, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM: *

The Federal Public Defender appointed to represent Forrest Brandon Buxton has moved for leave to withdraw and has filed a brief in accordance with Anders v. California, 386 U.S. 738, 87 S.Ct. 1396, 18 L.Ed.2d 493 (1967). Buxton has not filed a response. Our independent review of the record and counsel’s brief discloses no non-frivolous issue for appeal. Accordingly, counsel’s motion for leave to withdraw is GRANTED, counsel is excused from further responsibilities herein, and the APPEAL IS DISMISSED. See 5th Cir. R. 42.2.

Pursuant to 5th Cir. R. 47.5, the court has determined that this opinion should not be published and is not precedent except under the limited circumstances set forth in 5th Cir. R. 47.5.4.
